olive oil
1 tin sweetcorn
1 carrot
1 packet beef strips
1 packet ginger paste
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
drizzle vinegar (white  wine or rice wine)
1 sachet Crispy Shallots
1 packet coriander

• Drain sweetcorn. Grate carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook ginger paste, sweet soy seasoning and beef strips, in batches until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove the pan from the heat. Return all beef to the pan, then add the honey. Toss to coat.


TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot, sweetcorn, mayonnaise and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.

• Divide slaw between bowls.
• Top with sweet soy-ginger beef, spooning over any remaining sauce from the pan.
• Sprinkle with crispy shallots and tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!